author: Angela Robinson Piñon
ai_summary_baseline: The San Rafael Police Advisory and Accountability Committee (PAAC) will hold a meeting on November 20, 2024, at 6:00 PM, both in person and virtually. The agenda includes discussions on homelessness, police technology, the 2025 meeting calendar, and the annual PAAC report. The October 16, 2024, PAAC meeting minutes, included in the document, covered presentations on homelessness and youth outreach.

author: Angela Robinson Piñon
ai_summary_baseline: These documents are meeting minutes and agendas from the San Rafael Police Accountability and Oversight Committee (PAAC). They detail discussions about police staffing, community engagement, and presentations of reports regarding use of force and other policing matters. The documents also include public comment procedures and information for future meetings.

author: Teresa Olson
ai_summary_baseline: The San Rafael Police Advisory and Accountability Committee (PAAC) will meet on November 20, 2024, at 6:00 PM to discuss topics including homelessness, policing, and the 2025 meeting schedule. The October 16, 2024 meeting minutes will be reviewed and approved, and public comment will be accepted. The meeting can be attended in person at San Rafael City Council Chambers or virtually via Zoom.
notes: Selected as English version of multilingual content (November-20-2024-x).
